<item>
            <title>[LU-9201] reduce llmount.sh startup time</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9201</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Loading the libcfs module is getting increasingly slow due to multiple checksum types being speed tested at startup (8 checksum types * 1s each).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Reduce the number of checksum algorithms checked at module load time to the ones that are actually need the speed, and reduce the amount of time taken to compute the checksum.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The mount_facet() code also gained a 5s sleep for &lt;em&gt;each&lt;/em&gt; target mounted when &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/20194&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/20194&lt;/a&gt; was landed, which slows down tests that reformat the filesystem a lot (like conf-sanity.sh) significantly, and is in any case an annoyance for developer testing.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
